{"PageNumber":17,"Angle":0,"RotatedAngle":0,"Height":817,"Width":1089,"OriginHeight":0,"OriginWidth":0,"Elements":[{"Index":0,"Type":"title","Text":"#  Essential Attributes of a Good Software i","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":29,"Y":72},"LeftTop":{"X":29,"Y":18},"RightBottom":{"X":690,"Y":72},"RightTop":{"X":690,"Y":18}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":-1,"group_type":""},{"Index":1,"Type":"title","Text":"##  Efficiency","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":94,"Y":212},"LeftTop":{"X":94,"Y":175},"RightBottom":{"X":220,"Y":212},"RightTop":{"X":220,"Y":175}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":-1,"group_type":""},{"Index":2,"Type":"paragraph","Text":"• Software should not make wasteful use of system resources such as memory and processor cycles. Efficiency therefore includes responsiveness, processing time, memory utilization, etc.","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":119,"Y":387},"LeftTop":{"X":119,"Y":232},"RightBottom":{"X":971,"Y":387},"RightTop":{"X":971,"Y":232}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":-1,"group_type":""},{"Index":3,"Type":"title","Text":"##  Acceptability","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":94,"Y":466},"LeftTop":{"X":94,"Y":429},"RightBottom":{"X":267,"Y":466},"RightTop":{"X":267,"Y":429}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":-1,"group_type":""},{"Index":4,"Type":"paragraph","Text":"• Software must be acceptable to the type of users for which it is designed. This means that it must be understandable, usable, and compatible with other systems that they use.","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":119,"Y":602},"LeftTop":{"X":119,"Y":485},"RightBottom":{"X":993,"Y":602},"RightTop":{"X":993,"Y":485}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":-1,"group_type":""},{"Index":5,"Type":"footer","Text":"12","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":1045,"Y":786},"LeftTop":{"X":1045,"Y":764},"RightBottom":{"X":1066,"Y":786